<paragraph id="D749C44D3807C20361A1FBEAEB0A1804" blockId="1.[151,1437,1099,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">
Described based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="AFE184DD3807C2036348FBEAECAE1A3C" box="[638,749,1099,1125]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="15320AAF3807C20363CDFBEAED291A3F" box="[763,874,1099,1126]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C203624DFBEAEA411A3C" author="Berg, F. G. C." box="[891,1026,1099,1125]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" pagination="392 - 396" refId="ref5574" refString="Berg, F. G. C. (1883) Zur Pampa-Fauna. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 44, 392 - 396." type="journal article" year="1883">Berg (1883)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C2036592FBEAEB621A3C" authorityName="Dohrn" authorityYear="1882" box="[1188,1313,1099,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venturae">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C2036592FBEAEB621A3C" box="[1188,1313,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">S. venturae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C2036469FBEAEE9E1AD0" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbignyi">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C2036469FBEAEE9E1AD0" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">S. orbignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(translated): “I especially mention these wide distributional districts, because often one and the same species, or varieties of a species, which originated from 
<collectingRegion id="15320AAF3807C2036380FB32ED5D1AF4" box="[694,798,1171,1197]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
and Patagonia, are set up as new species because of the widely scattered localities. Even the species of our revered President, 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C20362ABFB16EA2D1A88" authority="Venturae, I" authorityName="Venturae, I" box="[925,1134,1207,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C20362ABFB16EA1A1A88" box="[925,1113,1207,1233]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Sypilus Venturae</emphasis>
, I
</taxonomicName>
suspect is only a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C20361A1FB7AEF5B1AAC" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1840" box="[151,280,1243,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbignyi">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C20361A1FB7AEF5B1AAC" box="[151,280,1243,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">S. Orbignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Guér.” Thus, 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C2036081FB7AEC7C1AAC" author="Berg, F. G. C." box="[439,575,1243,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" pagination="392 - 396" refId="ref5574" refString="Berg, F. G. C. (1883) Zur Pampa-Fauna. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 44, 392 - 396." type="journal article" year="1883">Berg (1883)</bibRefCitation>
did not formalize the synonymy, as usually has been recorded. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C20361A1FB5EEF6C1B40" author="Dohrn, C. A." box="[151,303,1279,1305]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" pagination="427 - 428" refId="ref5840" refString="Dohrn, C. A. (1883) Exotisches. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 44 (10 - 12), 427 - 428." type="journal article" year="1883">Dohrn (1883)</bibRefCitation>
not only keep the species as valid, but also corrected the 
<typeStatus id="084D7AEF3807C2036292FB5EED971B40" box="[932,980,1279,1305]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">type</typeStatus>
locality (translated): “It has already been designated by Professor Berg, p. 392, as a candidate for death, so that I can bury him without conscience in the ocean of synonymy. But I have received a second specimen from the same source, from 
<collectingCountry id="AFE184DD3807C2036518FAE6EA861B38" box="[1070,1221,1351,1377]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
<collectingRegion id="15320AAF3807C20365FBFAE6EB7B1B38" box="[1229,1336,1351,1377]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
, and it is precisely this second specimen that brings the former to its specific value. For, first, it is smaller and slimmer than the latter, so it refutes the reasons that arise from the stature, but second, the sender now gives me a correction of the locality. Not both from 
<collectingRegion id="15320AAF3807C20360ABFA12EC461B94" box="[413,517,1459,1485]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
but from Chacabuco in the province of 
<collectingRegion id="15320AAF3807C20362F7FA12EA1A1B94" box="[961,1113,1459,1485]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
, both specimens were found. The antennae and legs of the second smaller specimen are not so blackish brown, but brighter than those of the one sent earlier, but they do not show the yellowish-green color of these parts of the body remotely, as they do on the plate in Plate 20, fig. 
<quantity id="100E69A83807C20360BBF9BEEFFA1860" box="[397,441,1567,1593]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
Voyage de d’Orbigny.” 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C20363FBF9BEED101863" author="Dias, M. M." box="[717,851,1567,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" pagination="115 - 139" refId="ref5724" refString="Dias, M. M. (1986) Revisao da subfamilia Anoplodermatinae. Parte II. Tribo Anoplodermatini. Generos: Acanthomigdolus Bruch, 1911, Paramigdolus, gen. n., Anoploderma Guerin-Meneville, 1840, Sypilus Guerin-Meneville, 1840. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 30 (1), 115 - 139." type="journal article" year="1986">Dias (1986)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out the correction of the 
<typeStatus id="084D7AEF3807C20365E7F9BEEB421860" box="[1233,1281,1567,1593]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">type</typeStatus>
locality from 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C20361A1F9E2EF771804" author="Dohrn, C. A." box="[151,308,1603,1629]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" pagination="427 - 428" refId="ref5840" refString="Dohrn, C. A. (1883) Exotisches. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 44 (10 - 12), 427 - 428." type="journal article" year="1883">Dohrn (1883)</bibRefCitation>
. It was Lameere (1902b) who formalized the synonymy between 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C2036524F9E2EAD31804" authorityName="Dohrn" authorityYear="1882" box="[1042,1168,1603,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venturae">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C2036524F9E2EAD31804" box="[1042,1168,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">S. venturae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="10F6BFCE3807C20365F1F9E2EB011804" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1840" box="[1223,1346,1603,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sypilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbignyi">
<emphasis id="E582185F3807C20365F1F9E2EB011804" box="[1223,1346,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">S. orbignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9FEC97C63807C20361F1F9C6ED0B18FC" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" type="description">
<paragraph id="D749C44D3807C20361F1F9C6ED0B18FC" blockId="1.[151,1437,1099,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">
Monné (2018c) and 
<bibRefCitation id="B367B9BC3807C203609EF9C6ED4E18D8" author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H." box="[424,781,1639,1665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521" refId="ref7297" refString="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2018) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 31 January 2019)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte (2018)</bibRefCitation>
reported the 
<typeStatus id="084D7AEF3807C20362A8F9C6EA4318D8" box="[926,1024,1639,1665]" pageId="1" pageNumber="521">holotype</typeStatus>
being deposited in the CMSP collection. However, the specimen currently is in ZMPA collection.
</paragraph>
